    <div class="prose">
      <div class="te-block">
        <p>నేను laparoscopic approach routine గా prefer చేయను, automatic గా recommend చేయను. Case-by-case assessment అవసరం. Tumour location, stage, patient fitness, prior surgeries అన్నీ consider చేస్తాను.</p>
        <p>Multiple RCTs (randomised controlled trials) confirm: suitable colon cancer cases లో laparoscopic surgery oncological outcomes open surgery కి equivalent. COST trial, CLASICC trial, COLOR trial అన్నీ ఇది confirm చేశాయి. Rectal cancer TME కి laparoscopic approach careful case selection అవసరం.</p>
        <p>MIE (Minimally Invasive Esophagectomy) పైన Journal of Minimal Access Surgery 2021 లో publish చేశాను. Charité Berlin లో training లో specifically MIE practise చేశాను.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="en-block">
        <p>I do not routinely prefer the laparoscopic approach or recommend it automatically. Case-by-case assessment is needed. Tumour location, stage, patient fitness and prior surgeries are all considered.</p>
        <p>Multiple RCTs confirm that laparoscopic surgery gives oncological outcomes equivalent to open surgery in suitable colon cancer cases. The COST trial, CLASICC trial and COLOR trial all confirm this. Laparoscopic TME for rectal cancer requires careful case selection.</p>
        <p>I published on MIE (Minimally Invasive Esophagectomy) in the Journal of Minimal Access Surgery 2021. During my training at Charité Berlin, I specifically practised MIE.</p>
      </div>
